Description: CVE-2026-41992 - gzip: don't mishandle .lzh after .Z
 A buffer overflow has been fixed when decompressing an .lzh file
 after decompressing a .Z file.  Fix in unlzh.c (read_c_len) to clear
 the left and right arrays when n == 0, which is needed in case those
 arrays were reused from a previous LZW decompression.
 .
 Reported by Michal Majchrowicz.
 .
 The NEWS entry has been adapted to fit the trixie (1.13) NEWS
 structure by placing the note under the existing "Bug fixes" section
 of release 1.13.
Origin: upstream, https://cgit.git.savannah.gnu.org/cgit/gzip.git/commit/?id=63dbf6b3b9e6e781df1a6a64e609b10e23969681
Author: Paul Eggert <eggert@cs.ucla.edu>
